    (Poisson: <r>≈0.386, GOE: <r>≈0.536, GUE: <r>≈0.603)
    → Closest to: GUE
    Q_2 (2nd mode) = 0.2500 (O(1), not O(m²))
    Max bulk Q = 281335.2478


======================================================================
8. PARTITION FUNCTION AS FREDHOLM DETERMINANT
======================================================================

In LPP and TASEP, the partition function can be written as a
Fredholm determinant: Z = det(I - K) where K is an integral operator.

For our tournament: H(T) = p · ∏(1+Q_k) · A where A = amplification.
The F-product ∏(1+Q_k) IS a finite Fredholm determinant:
  F = det(I + DD*) / (1+m²)
where D is the diagonal matrix of Dirichlet kernel values.

This connects to the Borodin-Okounkov identity:
  det(I - K) = exp(Σ tr(K^n)/n) [when K is trace class]

In our case:
  log F = Σ_{k=1}^{m} log(1+Q_k)
  = Σ_{k=1}^m Σ_{n=1}^∞ (-1)^{n+1} Q_k^n / n
  = Σ_{n=1}^∞ (-1)^{n+1} S_n / n  where S_n = Σ Q_k^n

This is the PLETHYSTIC LOGARITHM! And S_n are the power-sum
symmetric functions of the eigenvalues.


  p=7: F_p = 13.00
    log F (exact) = 2.564949
    Plethystic (9 terms) = -193820.807143
    Power sums S_n: ['6.00', '26.00', '129.00', '650.00', '3281.00']
    S_1 = ΣQ = 6.0000 = m(m+1)/2 = 6.0

  p=11: F_p = 89.00
    log F (exact) = 4.488636
    Plethystic (9 terms) = -677454559.517859
    Power sums S_n: ['15.00', '155.00', '1884.00', '23219.00', '286555.00']
    S_1 = ΣQ = 15.0000 = m(m+1)/2 = 15.0

  p=13: F_p = 233.00
    log F (exact) = 5.451038
    Plethystic (9 terms) = -13790880215.658352
    Power sums S_n: ['21.00', '301.00', '5103.00', '87677.00', '1508401.00']
    S_1 = ΣQ = 21.0000 = m(m+1)/2 = 21.0


======================================================================
SYNTHESIS: FIVE-WAY DICTIONARY
======================================================================

Tournament    | TASEP          | LPP              | RMT            | Algebraic
------------- | -------------- | ---------------- | -------------- | ---------
Vertex i      | Site i         | Node (i,t)       | Eigenvalue i   | Root α_i
Edge i→j      | Hop i→j        | Edge weight       | Level repul.   | Root diff
Connection S  | Hop range      | Edge distribution | Potential      | Weyl group
HP σ          | Trajectory     | Geodesic         | Eigenstate     | Weyl element
H(T)          | Partition fn Z | # geodesics      | det(I+K)       | |W|
Q_k           | Bethe root     | Shape param      | λ_k            | Character val
F_p = ∏(1+Q)  | Free energy    | Weight gen fn    | Fredholm det   | Schur fn
A (amplif.)   | Interaction    | Multiplicity     | Tracy-Widom    | Correction
Interval S    | Nearest-neigh  | Directed lattice | GUE            | Longest element
Paley S       | Long-range     | Random graph     | CUE            | Coxeter element
m = (p-1)/2   | Density        | Dimension        | Matrix size    | Rank
φ (growth)    | Current        | Shape limit      | Spectral edge  | Coxeter number
8/π² (distrib)| Occupation     | Aspect ratio     | Bulk density   | Root density
